---
import LegalPage from "../components/LegalPage.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Aizen"
  description="Privacy Policy for Aizen, a macOS developer tool by Vivy Technologies Co., Limited."
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
  ogType="article"
>
  <LegalPage title="Privacy Policy" lastUpdated="April 10, 2026">
    <section>
      <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        Vivy Technologies Co., Limited ("we", "our", or "us") operates Aizen. This Privacy Policy
        explains how we handle information related to the website, support requests, and official app
        distributions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Website Information</h2>
      <p>
        We use Umami Analytics, a privacy-focused analytics service, to collect anonymous usage
        statistics on our website. This includes page views and general interaction data. No personal
        information is collected or stored through analytics.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. App Data</h2>
      <p>
        Aizen is a macOS application for managing Git worktrees with integrated terminal, file
        browser, web browser, and AI agent support. All project data, terminal sessions, and agent
        conversations are stored locally on your device.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. License Information</h2>
      <p>
        If you purchase Aizen Pro, we collect your email address and payment information through our
        payment processor (Stripe). License keys are stored securely to validate your subscription.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Support Requests</h2>
      <p>
        If you contact support, we receive the information you send us, such as your email address,
        device details, screenshots, logs, and reproduction notes. We use that information only to
        respond to your request and improve the product.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. How We Use Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To provide and maintain the website and app</li>
        <li>To process transactions and send related information</li>
        <li>To troubleshoot bugs and support requests</li>
        <li>To improve the application and workflows</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations when required</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Data Storage and Security</h2>
      <p>
        Your data is stored securely and we implement appropriate technical measures to protect
        against unauthorized access. We do not sell or share your personal information with third
        parties except as necessary to provide our services.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        You may contact us to ask what support-related information we hold, or request deletion where
        applicable. You can also remove locally stored app data by deleting the app and related files
        on your device.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact
        <a href="mailto:dev@aizen.win"> dev@aizen.win</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </LegalPage>
</BaseLayout>
